{"url": "https://people.com/awards/golden-globes-2018-mariah-carey-took-meryl-streep-seat/", "text": "Mariah Carey had a little mix-up on the way back to her seat during a commercial break at the Golden Globes on Sunday night, accidentally landing in the seat of another entertainment legend: Meryl Streep.\n\nThe 47-year-old singer, who recently performed on Dick Clark\u2019s New Year\u2019s Rockin\u2019 Eve with Ryan Seacrest, tweeted from the Globes audience about her encounter with The Post star, who was nominated for best actress.\n\nAccording to Carey, she grabbed the closest empty seat she could find as a commercial break came to a close while she was returning from the bathroom \u2014 ending up next to Post director Steven Spielberg.\n\n\u201cGot caught mingling on the way to the loo during a commercial break.. took the first seat available, happens to be right next to Steven Spielberg,\u201d Carey wrote.\n\n\u201cCut to next commercial break,\u201d she continued, \u201cguess who comes back to her seat\u2026\u201d\n\nBe sure to check out PEOPLE\u2019s full Golden Globes coverage to get the latest news on Hollywood\u2019s big night.\n\nRELATED PHOTOS: Making a Statement \u2014 See the Stars Wearing Black at the Golden Globes\n\nTo donate to the Time\u2019s Up Legal Defense Fund, which will provide subsidized legal support to women and men in all industries who have experienced sexual harassment, assault, or abuse in the workplace, visit its GoFundMe page. Learn more about Time\u2019s Up, an organization of women in entertainment combating sexual harassment and inequality, on its website.\n\nAll was well, though, as Carey and Streep, 68, shared a bit of banter about the confusion. (And maybe they got a drink from Tom Hanks?)\n\nIn her telling, Carey\u2019s apology was met with graciousness by Streep, who told her, \u201cYou can take my seat any time!\u201d\n\nTwitter followers couldn\u2019t get enough. As one wrote: \u201cTwo women at the top of their game!\u201d\n\nThe 75th annual Golden Globes were presented live on NBC from the Beverly Hilton in Beverly Hills, California, on Sunday.", "images": ["https://people.com/thmb/LztNjwaQ-ix4eK4edUooLhNiWi4=/800x533/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/anna-kepner-3-111025-c6a90b2f57474459a89ae04e296ec343.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/ahNrWCUAAT_xzAsCJIcmjiWDVzE=/343x228/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/helen-mirren-mobland-premiere-110525-b425e6484c2b4746ab495a8255cc8369.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/FfCEzDVicGIg0cY5gPcH3e4us64=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/jimi-westbrook-cma-awards-12-11925-68e926c1288d46dc8ab13c60f87a6e7e.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/9roC-YtZTUfDeOFxRtoSoPYtfCg=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/lorde-2025-LACMA-gracie-abrams-Paris-Fashion-Week-Megan-Moroney-am-i-okay-tour-110725-6364c2fd3f604bf0b315bbfd550d04e2.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/Kk5xblem4UUoqe-Ny6XceWyZykA=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/tom-cruise-16th-governors-awards-111725-1-14449dd9f79f49568ad0df6289ccb6c2.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/0UASPrG2EGRteRqV7vykMP9HCKk=/343x228/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/oscars-2017-wrong-best-picture-11725-500bf3e6b1704de4b1c595c17efc3e90.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/Ghw45H0tvXu9nKFXHwyxTuoGNm0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(733x0:735x2)/mariah-carey-2000-65d5db2392d140d89b2e8ce285e43362.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/VFI1rOmIoXtzxUkaG8prU__XslM=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Lainey-Wilson-2025-CMAs-111925-5-a07b40eaf39e4c8b8f3a88ea0810cc9f.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/svZr_sGNopVC5ATSNr5H3PIPEsY=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Vince-Gill-2025-CMAs-111925-2-a7c0e332f563415c8e6957d27b5499b2.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/qC1I_RAkiiTEt3CDq0N72YKdKbI=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/dolly-parton-16th-gove